724443f-a.text:
West End Avenue, west side, north from 73rd Street, showing the rear of the residence and grounds of Charles M. Schwab, from 73rd to 74th Streets, and the new Hotel Esplanade on the N.W. corner of 74th Street.

About 1920.

Underwood & Underwood, Photographers.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
Neg. #1150
724443f-a.folder: West End Avenue & 73rd Street (West), Manhattan, NY

724442f-a.text:
West End Avenue, S.W. corner of 73rd Street, showing 267-79 West End Avenue, old residences built around 1890. To the right may be seen part of the new Hudson Towers apartment house, nearing completion on the N.W. corner of 72nd Street.

June 1925.
724442f-a.folder: West End Avenue & 73rd Street (West), Manhattan, NY

714416f-a.text:
The Level Club, on W.73rd St., bet. Broadway & West End Ave., the 1st Masonic club house and hotel in America, built at a cost of $4,300,000, which will be officially opened on Saturday, Nov.12, with a civic parade and banquet.

Seiden Films, 729 7th Ave., N.Y.C.

May 31, 1931.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
